This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the detection and prevention of network intrusion. It also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate data for training the classifier could place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), which also involves the use of GANs for image generation.
